social_posts.post_text: Some selects from my project “When We Break, How We Shine” a series of landscape photographs made throughout my home state of Alabama during the Covid-19 pandemic, from March of 2020 until September of 2022. Full series is up on my website, link in my bio.

Pleased to be featured as an honorable mention and to have selects from my project “When We Break, How We Shine” included for the Fall 2022 @innovategrant. Swing through their website to check out the great work on display.

social_posts.post_text: Pleased to learn that my first monograph “All the Place You’ve Got” will enter the permanent collection of the Morris Museum of Art in Augusta Georgia. Huge thank you to the small team over at @cattywampuspress for their continued support and love over the years.

Hello! I have an exhibition coming up at the end of the year (more details down the road) but I need to purchase a bunch of frames. So to support this I am selling 8x10 prints of these 3 images on exhibition fiber paper, $50 a piece, edition of 15. If interested please shoot me a DM!
i like revisiting old work from time to time to remind myself of what i used to see when i still had fresh eyes

On Friday I bore witness to the birth of my beautiful daughter Eden Mercy Ronan Lunsford. I am so proud of and grateful for my wife @kronannn who is an immensely incredible woman and partner. Eden is perfect and I couldn’t be happier and more loved in this moment than how I feel currently.

A photo series and conversation from @devinluns and @markplasma on photography and the grotesque. Check out the complete series and dialogue now on bruisermag.com

My good friend @markplasma and I collaborated on a photo series and had a conversation about the grotesque, photography, and pro wrestling. “All This Time You Thought I Was Good” is up on @bruiser_mag, swing through and give it a look.
